The '''Gabinete de Urbanização Colonial''' (1944-1974) of Portugal was a government office responsible for [[urban planning]] in Portuguese [[Portuguese Empire|colonies]] in Africa and Asia. It began operating in 1945. In 1951 it became the '''Gabinete de Urbanização do Ultramar''', and in 1957 the '''Direcção de Serviços de Urbanismo e Habitação''' of the [[Overseas Ministry (Portugal)|Overseas Ministry]] public works department.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Luanda and Maputo: Accounts of the Two Capitals in Urban Heritage Discourse |author= [[Walter Rossa]] |year= 2016 |url=http://hdl.handle.net/10316/34093 |via=[[Universidade de Coimbra]] |journal= Journal of Lusophone Studies |volume=1 |issn=2469-4800 |publisher= American Portuguese Studies Association }} {{open access}}</ref> Staff included Joao A. de Aguiar, Rogerio Cavaca, and Pinto Coelho.<ref>{{cite book|editor= Carlos Nunes Silva |title= Urban Planning in Lusophone African Countries |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gnW1CwAAQBAJ|year=2015 |publisher=Ashgate |location=UK |isbn=1472444884 }}</ref>
