The '''Kielanowski Institute of Animal Physiology and Nutrition''' is a Polish [[agricultural research]] organization in [[Jabłonna, Legionowo County|Jabłonna]], near [[Warsaw]], Poland. It is part of the [[Polish Academy of Sciences]]. It publishes a [[scientific journal|journal]], ''[[Journal of Animal and Feed Sciences]]'', and [[monograph]]s on various topics.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Journal of Animal and Feed Sciences |title=2015 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ifzz.pl/pl/oferta/wydawnicza|title=Oferta Wydawnicza - Instytut Fizjologii i Żywienia Zwierząt PAN - IFZZ|last=User|first=Super|access-date=2018-03-15|language=pl-pl}}</ref>
== History ==
The institute was established in 1955 to conduct scientific research into the [[physiology]] and [[nutrition (animal)|nutrition]] of [[Livestock|farm animal]]s. The founder of the institute and its first director was Jan Kielanowski, whose name was given to the institute in 1990.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ifzz.pl/pl/instytut/historia|title=Historia - Instytut Fizjologii i Żywienia Zwierząt PAN - IFZZ|last=User|first=Super|access-date=2018-03-15|language=pl-pl}}</ref>
Institute directors: * Jan Kielanowski (1955–1974) * Stanisław Buraczewski (1974–1986) * Bernard Barcikowski (1987–1990) * Teresa Żebrowska (1990–1999) * Romuald Zabielski (1999–2003) * Jacek Skomiał (2003–2011, 2015–) * Tomasz Misztal (2011–2015)
